package.json
> starting point of application
> meta data
> packages 
> script


>>>>>>><<<<<<<<
Step to generate package.json
>>>>>>><<<<<<<<

*Node must be install in system (node -v)
> navigate to folder where you want package.json
> npm init
> answer all question
> type "yes"

>>>>>>><<<<<<<<
Step to install package/node_modules/dependency
>>>>>>><<<<<<<<
> navigate to folder where you want to install
> npm i packagename / npm install packagename


npm i 

>>>>>>><<<<<<<<
Step to generate react app 
>>>>>>><<<<<<<<
#Window
### One Time in one System ####
> open cmd as admin
> npm i -g create-react-app

### Next EveryTime you want new application ####
> Go Inside folder where you want application using cmd
> create-react-app appname
-------------------------------------
#Mac/Linux
### One Time in one System ####
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g create-react-app

### Next EveryTime you want new application ####
> Go Inside folder where you want application using terminal
> create-react-app appname

>>>>>>><<<<<<<<
Step to run react app 
>>>>>>><<<<<<<<
> Go Inside the application using cmd/terminal
> npm start
> http://localhost:3000


........components.........
> Class components
# Heavy as compare to Functional
# Logical Component
# can be use for display as well as api call and logics
# We can maintain state in class Component

> Functional components
# light in weight
# dumb Component
# Use for display Purpose
# We cannot maintain State in Functional

State > Act like a local variable
Props> help to transfer data between nested Component


